  "prompt": "How can I change the \"Ok Google\" phrase to something else in a Nexus 6?",
  "response": "On a Nexus 6, you cannot change the \"Ok Google\" activation phrase to something else directly within the Google Assistant settings. The wake phrase is hardcoded to \"Ok Google.\" However, you can use the following alternative:\n\n1. **Access Assistant Settings**:\n   - Open the Google app on your Nexus 6.\n   - Tap on the **More** option (three horizontal lines or dots) at the bottom right.\n   - Go to **Settings**.\n\n2. **Voice Match**:\n   - Tap on **Voice**.\n   - Select **Voice Match**.\n   - Here, you can set up Voice Match for recognizing your voice.\n\nWhile you cannot change the phrase, you can control various other settings, such as personalization.\n\nIf you're looking for alternatives to activating Google Assistant, you might consider exploring third-party apps that support different command phrases, but do be cautious with the permissions required by such apps. \n\nKeep in mind that future updates to Android or Google Assistant may change this capability or allow for more customization.",
